# Static-host edge rules (e.g. Netlify) for API proxy during standalone frontend deploys.
# Canonical local/prod for this monorepo is root Docker Compose (see repo README).
# Proxy all /api/* requests to the configured API host
# This allows the frontend to use relative URLs like /api/server
# Using HTTPS with Let's Encrypt trusted certificate
# Force proxy with 200 status to avoid redirect loop

/api/*  https://api.numz.site/api/:splat  200!
/socket.io/*  https://api.numz.site/socket.io/:splat  200!
